qas.question: What is the name of the New York City department that operates the park system?

answers.text: New York City Department of Parks and Recreation

qas.question: What is the state office that operates New York City parks?

answers.text: New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation

qas.question: What federal service operates New York City parks?

context: The City of New York has a complex park system, with various lands operated by the <a2_0>National Park Service<a2_0/>, the <a1_0>New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation<a1_0/>, and the <a0_0>New York City Department of Parks and Recreation<a0_0/>.
